{"questionId":"17379","questionHtml":"<p>Given that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,75^\\circ&nbsp; = q\"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <msup> <mn>75</mn> <mo>∘</mo> </msup> <mo>=</mo> <mi>q</mi> </math></span>, show that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,105^\\circ&nbsp; =&nbsp; - q\"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <msup> <mn>105</mn> <mo>∘</mo> </msup> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mi>q</mi> </math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,105^\\circ&nbsp; = {\\text{cos}}\\left( {180^\\circ&nbsp; - 75^\\circ } \\right) =&nbsp; - {\\text{cos}}\\,75^\\circ \"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <msup> <mn>105</mn> <mo>∘</mo> </msup> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>180</mn> <mo>∘</mo> </msup> <mo>−</mo> <msup> <mn>75</mn> <mo>∘</mo> </msup> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <msup> <mn>75</mn> <mo>∘</mo> </msup> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" =&nbsp; - q\"> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mi>q</mi> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept arguments using the unit circle or graphical/diagrammatical considerations.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17379","referenceCode":"19N.1.AHL.TZ0.H_9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that cos 75 ∘ = q , show that cos 105 ∘ = − q .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber